  <p class="last-updated">Last updated: June 2026 &nbsp;|&nbsp; Applies to: ScaniT (Android &amp; iOS)</p>

 

  <div class="card">

    <h3>1. Introduction</h3>

    <p>ScaniT ("the App", "we", "our") is a document scanning application developed and maintained by Doron ("the Developer"). This Privacy Policy explains what information the App collects, how it is used, and what rights you have as a user. By downloading or using the App, you agree to the terms described in this document.</p>

  </div>

 

  <div class="card">

    <h3>2. Information We Collect</h3>

    <p>The App does <strong>not collect, transmit, or store any personal data</strong> on external servers. All content created within the App — including scanned documents, PDF files, images, and signatures — is stored exclusively on your device's local storage. We have no access to this data at any time.</p>

  </div>

 

  <div class="card">

    <h3>3. No Third-Party Data Sharing</h3>

    <p>We do not sell, rent, trade, or share any user data with third parties. The App does not integrate advertising networks, analytics platforms, or data brokers. No information about your usage, behavior, or content is transmitted to any external party.</p>

  </div>

 

  <div class="card">

    <h3>4. Device Permissions</h3>

    <p><strong>Camera:</strong> Used solely to capture document images and scan QR codes within the App. The camera is never activated in the background or without explicit user action.<br><br>

    <strong>Photo Library / Gallery:</strong> Used solely to allow you to import existing images for scanning. No images are accessed, copied, or uploaded without your explicit action.</p>

  </div>

 

  <div class="card">

    <h3>5. File Sharing</h3>

    <p>PDF files and documents are shared exclusively when you explicitly initiate a share action within the App. The App never shares or transmits files automatically or without your direct consent.</p>

  </div>

 

  <div class="card">

    <h3>6. Data Security</h3>

    <p>Since all data remains on your device, the security of your files is governed by your device's own security mechanisms (screen lock, encryption, etc.). We recommend keeping your device software up to date and using a secure screen lock to protect your documents.</p>

  </div>

 

  <div class="card">

    <h3>7. Children's Privacy</h3>

    <p>The App is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect any personal information from children. If you believe a child has used the App in a way that raises privacy concerns, please contact us immediately.</p>

  </div>

 

